				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I just got the Book of Darkness from the tower people in Lake Rathe.  Had three people (me, 47th Necromancer, a 46th necromancer, and a 55th level cleric).  I have had the note from Vurgo for a long time.  We decided to get the book when we were camping the epic dw goblin below the island for the cleric.  <BR>
<BR>
We got buffed up and pulled up pets.  The cleric targeted the wizard (49th level, i believe), the 46th necro targeted the woman, and I targeted her pet (earth elemental).  The cleric started with stunning the wizard, I st'd the pet, and the other necro used ignite bones on the woman mage.  <BR>
<BR>
Well, the wizard broke the stun and ran downstairs where he was stunned again, the pet never came, and one lifetap by me and the woman was dead.  I ran over and looted her body and got the book.  We then made a beeline for the rathe mountains zone while the wizzie was still stunned.<BR>
<BR>
It worked and I'll probably go to Permafrost to get the book of frost because I like the book's look and I already have 205 int.  I can get rid of the harvester and use the book with the additional 45 mana - I also cast allure of death a lot to top off mana - be nice for just right clicking.<BR>
<BR>
Kaallan
